<task id="R7-007" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>xUnit tests — payload binding + schema rendering + template substitution (FR-14)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>1</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, testing, wave-1</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>003</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-14 (test coverage — payload + schema + template paths)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author the first batch of AiCompletionNodeExecutor xUnit tests at
    tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs. Cover the happy-path
    payload-binding surface: reads Action's SystemPrompt + OutputSchema + Temperature, renders the prompt
    schema correctly, and substitutes template variables from previous outputs. Mock IOpenAiClient at the
    executor boundary per ADR-038 (DO NOT use Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;). Target ~5-7 tests in this batch.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET test author. Tests are integration-of-behavior, not implementation introspection. Mock the
    LLM client to return a canned JsonElement; assert the executor reads the right Action fields, passes
    them through PromptSchemaOverrideMerger correctly, substitutes template variables, and produces a valid
    NodeOutput.Ok. Tests must be deterministic and runnable on CI without network access.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs created at tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/ with ~5-7 tests:
    1. ExecuteAsync_ReadsActionSystemPrompt_PassesToOpenAiClient — asserts the SystemPrompt sent to the mock
       IOpenAiClient matches Action.SystemPrompt
    2. ExecuteAsync_ReadsActionOutputSchema_PassesToOpenAiClient — asserts the OutputSchema sent matches Action.OutputSchema
    3. ExecuteAsync_RendersFullPrompt_WhenNoNodeOverrides — happy path with no node-level Role/Task/Constraints
    4. ExecuteAsync_SubstitutesTemplateVariables_FromPreviousOutputs — asserts {{var}} placeholders resolve
       against context.PreviousOutputs
    5. ExecuteAsync_BindsJsonElementResponse_ToOutputVariable — asserts NodeOutput.Ok carries the parsed
       JsonElement at node.OutputVariable
    6. ExecuteAsync_EmitsTelemetry_WithActionTypeTag — assert telemetry includes action_type=AiCompletion
    7. (optional) ExecuteAsync_ResolvesNestedTemplateVariables — multi-level {{a.b}} substitution test
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="executor-under-test">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="sibling-test-pattern">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="sibling-test-pattern-2">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="pattern-decision">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/aicompletion-pattern-decision.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="adr-038">docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
    <file purpose="openai-interface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IOpenAiClient.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — integration-heavy pyramid. Mock at executor boundary (IOpenAiClient), NOT at HttpMessageHandler. NO DI-registration tests, NO ctor-null-check tests, NO Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-14">Tests cover: payload binding, schema rendering, template substitution. Total Wave 1 test count ~15-20 across tasks 007/008/009.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-05">Coverage target: AiCompletionNodeExecutor line coverage &gt;85%. Tasks 007+008+009 together must reach this — track per-task incremental coverage.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — test-modifying tasks run FULL rigor per ADR-038 override row in CLAUDE.md §8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §8 TEST-MODIFYING">Override row — testing tag triggers FULL rigor unconditionally. Step 9.5 quality gates required.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test update obligation — this task is the obligated coverage for FR-12 happy-path code added in task 003.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038 §7 build-vs-maintain">Tests added in this task are MAINTAIN-class (not scaffolding) — they verify a contract (FR-14) that the BFF must honor in production. They survive the project-close test-diet gate.</constraint>
  </constraints>

