    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: TEST-MODIFYING override (tag testing + tests/** modification per CLAUDE.md §8 override row — FULL rigor UNCONDITIONAL per ADR-038). Quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-14 + ADR-038 + docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md + tests/CLAUDE.md.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read sibling test file as template">
      Open tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutorTests.cs. Note: Moq usage for IOpenAiClient, NodeExecutionContext construction, NodeOutput.Ok assertions.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutorTests for simpler patterns">
      Open the sibling test file. Useful for: error aggregation, simple ExecuteAsync structure, FluentAssertions usage patterns.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Create AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs">
      File path: tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs
      Namespace: Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.Services.Ai.Nodes
      Class: public sealed class AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests
      Test fields:
      - Mock&lt;IOpenAiClient&gt; _openAiClient
      - PromptSchemaOverrideMerger _merger (real instance — pure logic)
      - Mock&lt;ILogger&lt;AiCompletionNodeExecutor&gt;&gt; _logger
      - AiCompletionNodeExecutor _sut (system under test)
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Write the 5-7 tests">
      Implement the goal-list tests:
      1. ExecuteAsync_ReadsActionSystemPrompt_PassesToOpenAiClient — _openAiClient.Verify the SystemPrompt parameter equals Action.SystemPrompt
      2. ExecuteAsync_ReadsActionOutputSchema_PassesToOpenAiClient — _openAiClient.Verify the OutputSchema parameter equals Action.OutputSchema
      3. ExecuteAsync_RendersFullPrompt_WhenNoNodeOverrides — context with empty ConfigJson; assert no override merge applied; SystemPrompt unchanged
      4. ExecuteAsync_SubstitutesTemplateVariables_FromPreviousOutputs — context.PreviousOutputs has {"matterName":"ACME"}; Action.SystemPrompt has "{{matterName}}"; assert "ACME" appears in the SystemPrompt sent to the LLM
      5. ExecuteAsync_BindsJsonElementResponse_ToOutputVariable — mock LLM returns JsonElement; assert NodeOutput.Ok.StructuredData equals that JsonElement; assert OutputVariable matches node.OutputVariable
      6. ExecuteAsync_EmitsTelemetry_WithActionTypeTag — use ActivityListener to capture activity; assert action_type tag present
      7. (optional) Nested template substitution test
      Use FluentAssertions per project convention.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Run tests">
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs
      Expect: all 5-7 tests pass.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Measure coverage delta">
      Run: dotnet test --collect:"XPlat Code Coverage" — generate coverage report scoped to AiCompletionNodeExecutor. Document the line-coverage % after this task in task notes; tracks toward NFR-05 &gt;85%.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs. Confirm all 5-7 tests cover the goal bullets + no ADR-038 banned patterns used.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the new test file. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-038 (test pyramid + banned patterns).
      Run `/test-diet` preview (read-only) — confirm tests classify as MAINTAIN per ADR-038 §7 (not SCAFFOLDING).
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 007 status complete; advance current-task.md (007 unblocks 008 and 009).
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs with conventional message.
      Example: test(bff/r7): payload binding + schema rendering + template substitution (Wave 1 task 007, FR-14)
    </step>
  </steps>

